
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ietf-rpsec-bgpsecrec-10.txt'>
    <title>"BGP Security Requirements", Blaine Christian, Tony Tauber</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ietf-rpsec-bgpsecrec-10.txt</link>
    <description>The security of BGP, the Border Gateway Protocol, is critical to the proper operation of large-scale internetworks, both public and private.  While securing the information transmitted between two BGP speakers is a relatively easy technical matter, securing BGP, as a routing system, is more complex.  This document describes a set of requirements for securing BGP and the routing information carried within BGP.</description>
    <dc:date>2008-11-02T23:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
